h3. Issue Summary

Jira Service Management throws Java NullPointerException and/or Null JSON Objects when removing a custom field context from a project and leaving the same custom field in the screen of the request type.
h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Create a Service Management Project;
 # Create a Custom Field with choices (checkboxes, radio button, select list);
 # Associate the custom field to the project created screen;
 # Create a Request Type and add the custom field to its screen;
 # Access the customer portal and verify that the request type woks;
 # Go to the Custom Field configuration and change its applicable context to a different project (not global context);
 # Now, go back to that projects customer portal and try to access that request type;

h3. Expected Results

You should be able to access the request type normally. 
h3. Actual Results

You click and you remain in the same page. 

